cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with optimizing learning in elections, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of positional scoring rules, which are commonly used in machine learning and data science, making cs.LG and cs.DS likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with voting and preference aggregation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GT (game theory). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data from participatory budgeting elections, which involves social and information networks, making cs.SI a possible sub-category.
